title: Grrr...
subTitle: Heartbroken and intoxicated, Rejimon stumbles into a lion's den at the zoo. Haridas, a guard, has to forcefully dive in to rescue him, earning media attention for the blunder.

title: Kabali
subTitle: A man spends 25 years in prison for fighting against oppression. Old but still bloodthirsty, he decides to seek revenge against his enemies upon his release.

title: Yugapurushan
subTitle: Sree Narayan Guru is a social reformer who wishes to bring about a change in Kerala. He leads various reform movements to abolish the caste system in his state.

title: Pulival Kalyanam
subTitle: Harikrishnan is an adopted younger brother of Karunan. When Karunan loses his right hand in an accident, Harikrishnan decides to look after his family.

title: Kadha Parayumbol
subTitle: Balan, a barber, struggles to give his family a better living. However, his life changes when his old friend, who is a film star, comes to his village for a film shoot.

title: Pulimurugan
subTitle: A small village seeks help from a man with extraordinary force to protect them against man-eating tigers and the drug mafia.

title: Kantara
subTitle: When greed paves the way for betrayal, scheming and murder, a young tribal reluctantly dons the traditions of his ancestors to seek justice.

title: Bromance
subTitle: When Binto learns of his brother Shinto's disappearance, his search for Shinto leads him to collaborate with others, resulting in unforeseen turns, revelations, and memorable experiences.

title: Johny Johny Yes Appa
subTitle: Johny pretends to be a gentleman but is a thief who thrives on lies and betrayals. His life turns upside down after his encounter with Adam, an orphan.

title: Johny Johny Yes Appa
subTitle: Johny pretends to be a gentleman but is a thief who thrives on lies and betrayals. His life turns upside down after his encounter with Adam, an orphan.

title: Teja Bhai and Family
subTitle: Teja Bhai, a gangster falls in love with Vedhika, a simple girl. He has to leave his criminal life behind in order to seek her father's consent to marry her.

title: Paviyettante Madhurachooral
subTitle: The life of a well-reputed teaching couple in a village takes a complete turn one morning by the arrival of a 15-year-old boy.

title: Kadha Thudarunnu
subTitle: Vidyalakshmi struggles to lead a normal life with her daughter after the sudden death of her husband. However, her world transforms after meeting Preman, an auto-rickshaw driver.

title: Chirikkum Thalika
subTitle: A comprehensive compilation of some of the best rib-tickling comedy scenes from various Malayalam movies featuring renowned actors and actresses.

title: Sunday Holiday
subTitle: Unni, who wishes to become a scriptwriter, learns that a director is hospitalised in his locality. He meets him to narrate his story about Amal, a heartbroken man who plans to start life afresh.

title: Thuruppugulan
subTitle: Menon buys land for his five-star hotel and asks his trusted employee, Sreedharan Unnithan, to take its charge. Years later, Unnithan gets Menon imprisoned in a fake case and Kunjumon helps him.

title: Android Kunjappan Version 5.25
subTitle: After Subramanian has to leave his aged father alone to go to Russia, he returns with a robot to take care of him. Even though hesitant at first, his father soon develops a strong bond with the robot.

title: Pachakuthira
subTitle: Anandakkuttan's life as a young artist takes a dramatic turn when he takes his autistic brother under his wing, leading to an unexpected yet heartwarming bond between them.

title: Christian Brothers
subTitle: When the daughter of a minister gets kidnapped, Christy is called upon to rescue her. Although he manages to save her, he himself gets embroiled in the kidnapper's murder.

title: Neymar
subTitle: Kunjava and his mate welcome a tail-wagging friend called Neymar, only to find their lives thrown into complete disarray.

title: Neymar
subTitle: Kunjava and his mate welcome a tail-wagging friend called Neymar, only to find their lives thrown into complete disarray.

title: Chandrolsavam
subTitle: Sreehari has returned home from Paris after six years. He tries to settle some scores and clear misunderstandings with his old friends before leaving his village.

title: Photographer
subTitle: When wildlife photographer Dijo saves a young native boy, Thammi, from the clutches of a corrupt police officer, he unwittingly sparks a perilous quest for justice, putting his own life at risk.

title: Kilometers and Kilometers
subTitle: A poor tour guide from Kerala takes an American client on a journey through India. During their travels, the changing landscapes and experiences help them reshape their understanding of each other.

title: Rappakal
subTitle: Saraswathiyamma is the head of a noble family that treats her servant Krishnan as one of her own sons. When her relatives conspire to sell her house, she and Krishnan set out to save it.

title: Sthanarthi Sreekuttan
subTitle: Sreekuttan and Ambadi present an intense rivalry concerning a school election. Soon, the contest fundamentally affects the classroom and involves pride and friendship.

title: Ohm Shanthi Oshaana
subTitle: Pooja Mathew, a spirited young girl, dreams about marrying only for love. Thus, she stops at nothing to impress Giri, who saved her once from a group of unruly men.

title: Oru Marubhoomikkadha
subTitle: Madhavan is an honest and hardworking man. However, when a rich man's daughter, Eliana, asks him to abduct her and demand a ransom from her father, his life turns upside down.

title: Vaazha
subTitle: Four misfits navigate societal and parental pressures as they enter adulthood. Subsequently, their heartfelt journey of self-discovery proves that love and acceptance always triumph over judgment.
